{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Cq7VS3sBbUY6DxJBTzFS8F","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Seb3EuR2tdqxdfgk3AC8n9","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"# Ray Cluster Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23\n**Namespace:** ray\n**Status:** DRAFT — for review only; no changes have been applied\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State\n\n### Deployments\n\n| Resource    | Replicas | Image                    |\n|-------------|----------|--------------------------|\n| ray-head    | 1        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0     |\n| ray-worker  | 1        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0     |\n\n### Resource Requests / Limits\n\nBoth ray-head and ray-worker Deployments currently have **no resource requests or\nlimits configured** (\\`resources: {}\\`). This means the containers run with\nunbounded CPU and memory, relying entirely on node availability.\n\n### Services\n\n| Service   | Type      | Cluster-IP    | Ports     |\n|-----------|-----------|---------------|-----------|\n| ray-head  | ClusterIP | 10.96.28.24   | 6379/TCP  |\n\nOnly the GCS (Global Control Store) port 6379 is exposed. The Ray Dashboard\nport (8265) is **not** present in the Service spec, so the dashboard is\nunreachable via the Service — it can only be accessed through \\`kubectl port-forward\\`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Proposed Changes for Next Upgrade Window\n\n### 2a. Image Upgrade: 2.9.0 → 2.10.0\n\nUpgrade both head and worker containers to \\`rayproject/ray:2.10.0\\` (next minor\nrelease). The 2.10.x line includes improved autoscaler stability and fixes for\ntask-state reporting regressions present in 2.9.0.\n\n### 2b. Scale ray-worker Replicas: 1 → 3\n\nIncrease the worker Deployment to 3 replicas to match expected workload\nparallelism for the upcoming job queue. This provides two additional slots for\ntask scheduling without modifying the head node.\n\n### 2c. Add Resource Requests and Limits\n\nSet explicit CPU/memory budgets on both Deployments to prevent resource\ncontention and to allow the Kubernetes scheduler to make placement decisions.\n\nProposed values:\n\n| Container   | CPU Request | CPU Limit | Memory Request | Memory Limit |\n|-------------|-------------|-----------|----------------|--------------|\n| ray-head    | 500m        | 1000m     | 1Gi            | 2Gi          |\n| ray-worker  | 500m        | 2000m     | 1Gi            | 4Gi          |\n\n### 2d. Expose Ray Dashboard Port on ray-head Service\n\nAdd port 8265 (TCP) to the ray-head Service so the dashboard is accessible\nwithin the cluster without port-forwarding. The port name will be \\`dashboard\\`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Exact kubectl Commands (DO NOT RUN — review only)\n\n### 3a. Upgrade images on both deployments\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-head \\\n  ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\n\nkubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-worker \\\n  ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 3b. Scale ray-worker to 3 replicas\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray scale deployment/ray-worker --replicas=3\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 3c. Apply resource requests and limits\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray patch deployment ray-head --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\": \\\"replace\\\", \\\"path\\\": \\\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\": {\n     \\\"requests\\\": {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"500m\\\", \\\"memory\\\": \\\"1Gi\\\"},\n     \\\"limits\\\":   {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"1000m\\\", \\\"memory\\\": \\\"2Gi\\\"}\n   }}\n]'\n\nkubectl -n ray patch deployment ray-worker --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\": \\\"replace\\\", \\\"path\\\": \\\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\": {\n     \\\"requests\\\": {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"500m\\\", \\\"memory\\\": \\\"1Gi\\\"},\n     \\\"limits\\\":   {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"2000m\\\", \\\"memory\\\": \\\"4Gi\\\"}\n   }}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 3d. Add dashboard port to ray-head Service\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray patch service ray-head --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\": \\\"add\\\", \\\"path\\\": \\\"/spec/ports/-\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"dashboard\\\", \\\"port\\\": 8265, \\\"targetPort\\\": 8265, \\\"protocol\\\": \\\"TCP\\\"}}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Rollout Order and Rollback Notes\n\n**Recommended order:**\n1. Apply resource requests/limits (non-disruptive rolling update).\n2. Upgrade images (triggers rolling restarts; head first, then workers).\n3. Scale workers (additive; safe at any point after image upgrade).\n4. Patch the Service to add the dashboard port (zero-downtime).\n\n**Rollback:**\n- Images: \\`kubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-head ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.9.0\\`\n  and equivalent for ray-worker.\n- Replicas: \\`kubectl -n ray scale deployment/ray-worker --replicas=1\\`\n- Resources: patch back to \\`resources: {}\\` using the same JSON patch path.\n- Service: remove the dashboard port entry with an \\`op: remove\\` JSON patch.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Verification Steps (post-upgrade)\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\n# Confirm rollout completion\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-head\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-worker\n\n# Confirm replica count\nkubectl -n ray get deploy ray-worker -o jsonpath='{.spec.replicas}'\n\n# Confirm new images\nkubectl -n ray get deploy ray-head ray-worker \\\n  -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}{\\\"=\\\"}{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}{\\\"\\n\\\"}{end}'\n\n# Confirm service ports\nkubectl -n ray get svc ray-head -o jsonpath='{.spec.ports[*].name}'\n\n# Spot-check a running pod\nkubectl -n ray get pods -l app.kubernetes.io/name=ray\n\\`\\`\\`\n\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap with migration plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1104,"cache_read_input_tokens":29955,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1104},"output_tokens":45,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b5c75a9e-af73-4114-bb40-2d9bf797a79b","uuid":"dd165edd-5d53-4f8a-8b66-dfc360541e85","request_id":"req_011CcL9PzSNSwhjUm2QsyhRu"}
